  "question_id": "dc07780b-7456-422d-b713-4c79decc42f7",
  "short_text": "Diamond",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print a **Diamond** of `(2 * N) - 1` rows using stars (`*`).\r\n\r\n```\r\n   *\r\n  * *\r\n * * *\r\n* * * *\r\n * * *\r\n  * *\r\n   *\r\n```\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nThere is a space after every star (`*`).\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Input\r\n\r\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Output\r\n\r\nThe output should be `(2 * N) - 1` rows containing stars (`*`) as a **Diamond** shown in the sample output.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n#### Explanation\r\n\r\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 3`,\r\n\r\n- Print stars (`*`) on **5** (`(2 * 3) - 1`) rows as shown in the given image.\r\n\r\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-diamond.png' widthPercent='50'/>\r\n\r\n<MultiLineNote>\r\nIn the given image,\r\n\r\n- The Empty box indicates a space (\" \").\r\n- The Star in the box indicates a star (\"*\").\r\n</MultiLineNote>\r\n\r\n```\r\n  * \r\n * * \r\n* * * \r\n * * \r\n  * \r\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "f80218cd-3cc2-4913-9d61-c1340b2a8aeb",
      "code_content": "n = int(input())\n\nk = n - 1\nfor i in range(1, n+1):\n    spaces = \" \" * k\n    stars = \"* \" * i\n    print(spaces+stars)\n    k = k - 1\n\nk = n\nfor i in range(1, n):\n    spaces = \" \" * i\n    stars = \"* \" * (k - i)\n    print(spaces+stars)\n\n",
      "language": "PYTHON39",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
